# corpus.md.example

This file is a TEMPLATE. Rename to `corpus.md` and fill it with your
top 20 LinkedIn posts (sorted by reactions, descending) so the
linkedin-copywriter skill drafts in YOUR voice, not a generic one.

The top 5 are the strongest voice anchors. The agent re-reads this
file before every draft to ground hook choice, body shape, and
vocabulary in your real writing.

## How to populate

Two paths:

**Path A · Connected to LinkedIn via Unipile or your platform:**

Ask Claude: "Read my last 20 LinkedIn posts via the LinkedIn API,
sort by reactions, and overwrite this file." If you have Unipile
configured, the curl block in `SKILL.md` (bottom) does the pull. The
agent then re-sorts and rewrites this file.

**Path B · Manual:**

Copy-paste your top 20 posts below using the format shown. Sort by
reaction count, descending. Preserve line breaks exactly as they
appear on LinkedIn · they're part of your rhythm.

## Refresh cadence

Quarterly. Voice drifts as you publish more, and stale corpora pull
the agent toward where you used to be, not where you are now.

## Format

Each post block:

---

### Post NN · <ReactionCount> reactions · <YYYY-MM-DD>

[full post text, line breaks preserved]

---

## Example block (delete before using)

